content: I'm planning a bird watching trip to the coastal area on April 1st and I was wondering if you could help me with some information on the best spots to see shorebirds and waterfowl during the spring migration. By the way, I just got back from a trip to the local park with my friend Sarah on March 10th, and we saw a flock of about 20 Canada Geese and a few Killdeer, which was really cool!
